, unfortunately.

00:11:16.210 --> 00:11:17.190
Yes.

00:11:17.200 --> 00:11:20.200
So a HTTP signature could reference, for example, a,

00:11:20.200 --> 00:11:26.310
uh, have, could include an ATURI that is

00:11:26.310 --> 00:11:29.370
in the, in the repository that has more involved contextual trust

00:11:29.370 --> 00:11:30.200
information.

00:11:30.200 --> 00:11:33.850
And the DIT documents themselves represent a whole lot of information

